snippet.title: Video Games: Myths vs. Facts
snippet.description: ... ( click to enlarge) ... ... For years now video games have been blamed for everything from learning disabilities to diminished social skills to heightened violent tendencies. Researchers have been able to substantiate many claims about video games (especially regarding children), but there are still plenty of misconceptions out there about them. Let’s try to understand what’s going on by taking a look at some common video game myths. ... ... Myth: Video games are primarily influencing adolescent boys. ... Fact: Yes, video games are popular among children, but it may surprise you that only 25 percent of gamers are under 18 years old. And perhaps even more surprising – 26 percent are over the age of 50. The assumption that adults don’t play video games is probably as prevalent as the stereotype that most gamers are men. While the latter is true overall, when you consider gamers under the age of 18, females outnumber males 33 to 20 percent.... ...
